JPMorgan’s Lau Hired by PineBridge to Head Asia Fixed Income

-- B y   A p r i l   L e e
-- 
2011-03-04T20:35:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/jpmorgan-s-lau-hired-by-pinebridge-to-head-fixed-income-in-asia.html
JPMorgan Chase & Co.’s Arthur Lau
was hired by PineBridge Investments, the wealth-management firm
sold by  American International Group Inc. (AIG)  last year, to be head
of fixed income for Asia excluding Japan.  Lau, based in  Hong Kong , will head a team of eight,
PineBridge said today in a  statement  posted on its website. He
was formerly a senior portfolio manager and head of Asian
credits at JPMorgan Asset Management in Hong Kong.  “I look forward to working closely with him as PineBridge
continues to grow its market position in Asia,” Rajeev Mittal,
head of emerging markets and international fixed income at
PineBridge, said in the statement.  PineBridge, based in  New York , had $82 billion in assets
under management as of Dec. 31, according to the statement.
Closely held Pacific Century Group purchased PineBridge from
AIG, where the firm was called AIG Global Investment Corp., for
$500 million in March.  Lau has been a director in credit research at  Barclays
Capital  in Singapore, PineBridge said. He has a bachelor’s
degree from Chinese University of Hong Kong and a master’s
degree in business administration from the University of Western
Ontario.  To contact the reporter on this story:
April Lee in New York at 
